1
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:08,160
So,

2
00:02:08,479 --> 00:02:12,520
the merchants and people of Ercheng went to Ruixi to borrow money.

3
00:02:12,920 --> 00:02:15,440
And Ruixi didn't care about age or gender.

4
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:17,440
As long as they were from Ercheng,

5
00:02:17,440 --> 00:02:20,240
they could borrow the amount of money they wanted.

6
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:21,920
At first,

7
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:24,200
the effect of the loans was really good.

8
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:24,840
Next.

9
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:26,720
A large number of new businesses were established.

10
00:02:26,720 --> 00:02:28,640
The living standards of the people

11
00:02:28,640 --> 00:02:30,770
also began to improve significantly.

12
00:02:31,120 --> 00:02:33,400
Ruixi spent a lot of silver

13
00:02:33,760 --> 00:02:38,280
to build many restaurants, hot springs, casinos, and brothels.

14
00:02:39,240 --> 00:02:42,720
For a time, the entire Er City was thriving.

15
00:02:43,120 --> 00:02:45,440
Magistrate Shen was also very pleased.

16
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:47,400
I see.

17
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:50,000
Master, what do you mean?

18
00:02:50,640 --> 00:02:51,640
It seems

19
00:02:52,720 --> 00:02:55,050
this demon is not only skilled in sorcery,

20
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:57,640
but also understands the human heart well.

21
00:02:57,640 --> 00:03:01,240
Before long, Er City emerged as a major commercial metropolis.

22
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:04,160
The prosperity is evident to all.

23
00:03:05,160 --> 00:03:07,560
But good fortune often hides misfortune.

24
00:03:07,560 --> 00:03:09,890
Disadvantages follow one after another.

25
00:03:12,440 --> 00:03:14,240
Good wine.

26
00:03:16,040 --> 00:03:17,360
Give me a kiss.

27
00:03:17,720 --> 00:03:19,240
Oh, what are you doing?

28
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:20,440
Hahaha.

29
00:03:24,440 --> 00:03:25,440
You can't kiss me.

30
00:03:25,920 --> 00:03:26,760
Stop it.

31
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:28,360
Greetings, Mr. Li.

32
00:03:31,720 --> 00:03:34,040
Oh, Brother Xiaoyou.

33
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:35,560
What brings you to me?

34
00:03:35,760 --> 00:03:41,200
Mr. Li, the loan from last month is due today.

35
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:46,920
I'm a bit tight on money lately.

36
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:49,440
How about you lend me another 50 taels?

37
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:51,840
I'll pay back 30 taels of the principal first,

38
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:54,520
and keep 20 taels for my business.

39
00:03:54,760 --> 00:03:57,160
As for the interest, we'll settle it later.

40
00:03:59,640 --> 00:04:00,840
Then I

41
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:04,760
won't disturb your enjoyment, Mr. Li.

42
00:04:04,760 --> 00:04:06,040
Haha.

43
00:04:06,040 --> 00:04:07,360
What are you talking about?

44
00:04:07,360 --> 00:04:10,240
Your Rui Mansion is the God of Wealth for all of Ercheng.

45
00:04:10,240 --> 00:04:12,300
Would you like to sit down for a drink?

46
00:04:13,360 --> 00:04:14,160
No, thanks.

47
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:18,320
I have to go collect loans elsewhere.

48
00:04:19,440 --> 00:04:20,839
Alright, haha.

49
00:04:21,399 --> 00:04:22,240
Farewell.

50
00:04:32,480 --> 00:04:33,680
Hahaha.

51
00:04:34,240 --> 00:04:36,240
Only a fool would return your money.

52
00:04:39,840 --> 00:04:40,840
Beauties.

53
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:44,520
Serve me the best wine and food.

54
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:47,040
Don't worry, sir. As long as you pay enough,

55
00:04:47,040 --> 00:04:48,400
anything is possible.

56
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:50,300
Here's a piece for you.

57
00:04:51,840 --> 00:04:53,000
Open it! Open it!

58
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:54,920
I'll definitely win this round.

59
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:58,120
Open! Open! Open!

60
00:05:03,640 --> 00:05:05,840
Lend me some money, some silver.

61
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:14,840
Hurry up.

62
00:05:14,840 --> 00:05:16,400
Yes, hurry.

63
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:19,720
Sir, come in and sit for a while.

64
00:05:21,160 --> 00:05:24,000
Thank you. Let's go.

65
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:24,860
Let's go, miss.

66
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:26,690
Let's play a little longer.

67
00:05:45,240 --> 00:05:46,040
Master.

68
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:49,640
Today, we still haven't collected half a tael of silver in loans,

69
00:05:49,640 --> 00:05:51,840
and we lent out another thousand taels.

70
00:05:52,440 --> 00:05:55,159
Human greed is like a trapped beast.

71
00:05:55,640 --> 00:05:56,840
Once unleashed,

72
00:05:57,159 --> 00:05:59,159
it's like a bursting river,

73
00:05:59,520 --> 00:06:01,120
unstoppable.

74
00:06:01,640 --> 00:06:03,800
Many disasters in the world

75
00:06:03,920 --> 00:06:05,400
stem from this.

76
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:48,000
I really didn't expect

77
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:50,520
the speed of Ercheng's collapse

78
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:53,600
to be much faster than I imagined.

79
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:55,530
Congratulations, Master.

80
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:58,320
Tomorrow, we will go to the yamen.

81
00:06:58,840 --> 00:07:03,040
We will help the common people once more.

82
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:07,120
Lady Ruixi, since you came to Ercheng,

83
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:10,120
your many good deeds have benefited our city greatly.

84
00:07:10,120 --> 00:07:11,560
I am deeply grateful.

85
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:14,960
I wonder what brings you here this time?

86
00:07:17,240 --> 00:07:19,400
Why are you sighing, Lady Ruixi?

87
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:22,000
Magistrate,

88
00:07:22,240 --> 00:07:25,920
I have been lending money in Ercheng for over a year.

89
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:29,720
Ercheng has indeed developed and prospered,

90
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:33,440
but the commoners rarely repay their loans.

91
00:07:34,360 --> 00:07:37,920
I thought the people here were honest,

92
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:42,800
but now I'm afraid I can't make ends meet.

93
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:44,159
Oh.

94
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:45,840
Is that so?

95
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:47,360
Indeed it is.

96
00:07:47,840 --> 00:07:50,600
Few people return the silver voluntarily.

97
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,200
Lady Ruixi,

98
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:58,570
your good deed of offering unsecured loans is commendable,

99
00:07:58,640 --> 00:08:01,240
but it is inevitable that some will get greedy.

100
00:08:01,240 --> 00:08:02,760
Do not worry, my lady.

101
00:08:02,840 --> 00:08:04,400
As the local magistrate,

102
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:06,440
I will personally inform the people

103
00:08:06,520 --> 00:08:08,840
and advise them to return the silver promptly.

104
00:08:08,840 --> 00:08:11,000
Since I am willing to offer unsecured loans,

105
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:13,800
I am naturally willing to take the risk.

106
00:08:14,440 --> 00:08:15,320
Then...

107
00:08:15,880 --> 00:08:18,200
We don't have much silver left in our residence.

108
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:20,360
If we continue to give out large loans,

109
00:08:20,360 --> 00:08:22,200
I'm afraid we won't be able to sustain it.

110
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:25,280
So I have to reduce the number of loans.

111
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:28,600
Starting tomorrow, I plan to

112
00:08:28,760 --> 00:08:31,600
only grant one loan for every ten households.

113
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:36,360
The choice of which household gets it will be left to the people.

114
00:08:36,760 --> 00:08:39,240
What do you think?

115
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:43,159
Well...

116
00:08:44,840 --> 00:08:46,720
Lady Ruixi, if you do this,

117
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:49,320
I'm afraid the people will fight for the spots.

118
00:08:50,440 --> 00:08:53,000
I have no other choice.

119
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:55,600
If the people borrowed and returned as promised,

120
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:57,160
I wouldn't have to do this.

121
00:08:58,400 --> 00:08:59,260
How about this?

122
00:08:59,760 --> 00:09:02,600
Once they have returned most of the silver,

123
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:07,200
I will open the loans again. What do you think?

124
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:11,650
If there's no other way,

125
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:13,280
let's do this for now.

126
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:19,640
Then thank you, my Lord.

127
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:21,160
Please.

128
00:09:23,760 --> 00:09:24,560
Please.

129
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:31,960
Magistrate,

130
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:33,720
this is inappropriate.

131
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:39,200
Ercheng's current booming prosperity

132
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:41,240
all depends on Lady Ruixi.

133
00:09:41,360 --> 00:09:44,360
I have also received numerous rewards from the court.

134
00:09:44,640 --> 00:09:46,170
At this critical juncture,

135
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:48,730
we should just follow her plan for now.

136
00:09:49,320 --> 00:09:50,120
Yes.

137
00:09:59,040 --> 00:09:59,760
So,

138
00:10:00,840 --> 00:10:02,840
the city fell into chaos after that,

139
00:10:03,960 --> 00:10:04,760
didn't it?

140
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:05,760
Exactly.

141
00:10:05,920 --> 00:10:08,360
The people were used to spending lavishly with the loans.

142
00:10:08,360 --> 00:10:09,890
Not only did they owe money,

143
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:12,060
but their savings were also emptied.

144
00:10:12,440 --> 00:10:14,000
It went from every household getting a loan

145
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,920
to one in ten.

146
00:10:15,920 --> 00:10:18,800
You can imagine how desperate everyone was.

147
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:20,520
To secure a loan quota,

148
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:21,480
the people

149
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:23,400
fought fiercely.

150
00:10:23,840 --> 00:10:26,440
And Magistrate Shen finally realized

151
00:10:26,440 --> 00:10:28,840
the malicious intent of Ruixi.

152
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:31,120
I was here first.

153
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:33,320
I was obviously here first.

154
00:10:33,760 --> 00:10:35,800
Stop fighting. Don't use violence.

155
00:10:36,480 --> 00:10:37,360
Stop fighting.

156
00:10:37,480 --> 00:10:38,400
Don't use violence.

157
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:43,240
Stop fighting.

158
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:44,640
Magistrate.

159
00:10:44,920 --> 00:10:45,760
Give it to me first.

160
00:10:45,760 --> 00:10:46,560
Young man,

161
00:10:46,560 --> 00:10:48,040
I want to see Lady Ruixi.

162
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:50,760
Master is waiting for you.

163
00:11:06,720 --> 00:11:07,840
Lady Ruixi.

164
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:12,040
County Magistrate,

165
00:11:12,040 --> 00:11:13,680
what brings you here?

166
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:15,600
Lady Ruixi, as you can see,

167
00:11:15,960 --> 00:11:17,960
the people outside are in an uproar.

168
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:21,000
What does that have to do with me?

169
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:24,840
It is their own greed that ruined them.

170
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:26,120
Be that as it may,

171
00:11:26,400 --> 00:11:28,040
as the lord of this city,

172
00:11:28,040 --> 00:11:30,560
I cannot bear to see the people slaughtering each other like this.

173
00:11:30,560 --> 00:11:32,440
So what do you want to do?

174
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:33,600
I believe that

175
00:11:33,600 --> 00:11:35,400
although the people are at fault in this matter,

176
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:37,560
the true root cause is you, Lady Ruixi.

177
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:38,640
In my opinion,

178
00:11:39,160 --> 00:11:41,400
we should stop lending money from today.

179
00:11:41,400 --> 00:11:43,520
Let the people be self-reliant

180
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:45,320
and delay the repayment of old debts.

181
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:47,640
This will solve the current difficulties.

182
00:11:47,640 --> 00:11:49,360
What do you think, my lady?

183
00:11:51,920 --> 00:11:56,360
We stop lending just because you say so?

184
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:04,280
Ping Jieqiang, Haihui.

185
00:13:04,280 --> 00:13:04,440
Ping Jieqiang.
